This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it focuses on language comprehension tasks and uses Neural Semantic Encoders (NSE) to achieve state-of-the-art results on standard machine comprehension benchmarks. Additionally, the paper also involves a hypothesis testing loop, which is a common approach in natural language processing research. 

The paper also involves the use of memory augmented neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning). 

Furthermore, the use of neural networks and machine learning techniques in the paper suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). However, these sub-categories are less likely as the paper primarily focuses on language comprehension tasks rather than computer vision tasks.
